.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3340217A403F5F14FCD4FC1A4A0E3F7C" blockId="40.[806,1422,911,1822]" pageId="40" pageNumber="307">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403F5F14FCD4FC1A4C8D3BC7" box="[806,1001,912,933]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="307">Taxonomic notes:</emphasis>
The adult of 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403F5F14FB60FC054B8F3BC7" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[1170,1259,911,933]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tapia">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403F5F14FB60FC054B8F3BC7" box="[1170,1259,911,933]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="307">C. tapia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403F5F14FC82FC244C813BA1" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[880,997,942,963]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albertoi">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403F5F14FC82FC244C813BA1" box="[880,997,942,963]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="307">C. albertoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
among bromeliad 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403F5F14FB30FC244A223BA1" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1846" box="[1218,1350,942,963]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403F5F14FB30FC244A223BA1" box="[1218,1350,942,963]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="307">Copestylum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Both are relatively dark species with a depression at the apex of the scutellum, black legs, upper half of the sides of the thorax bright yellow, and tergite 2 with large white spots. This colour pattern is also found in 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403F5F14FCBEFBCD4CA23C3E" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[844,966,1095,1116]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barbara">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403F5F14FCBEFBCD4CA23C3E" box="[844,966,1095,1116]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="307">C. barbara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403F5F14FC29FBCD4B133C3E" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[987,1143,1095,1116]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elizabethae">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403F5F14FC29FBCD4B133C3E" box="[987,1143,1095,1116]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="307">C. elizabethae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403F5F14FB33FBCD4C1E3C19" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xalapaensis">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403F5F14FB33FBCD4C1E3C19" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="307">Copestylum xalapaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but these three species do not have a scutellar depression. The same colour pattern is also found in 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403F5F14FC64FB294B773CDA" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[918,1043,1187,1208]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="conabioi">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403F5F14FC64FB294B773CDA" box="[918,1043,1187,1208]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="307">C. conabioi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the apex of the scutellum of that species has a ridge not a depression. 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403F5F14FAC7FB484AE93CB5" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[1333,1421,1218,1239]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tapia">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403F5F14FAC7FB484AE93CB5" box="[1333,1421,1218,1239]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="307">C. tapia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most easily separated from 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403F5F14FB46FB6B4A4D3C97" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[1204,1321,1248,1270]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albertoi">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403F5F14FB46FB6B4A4D3C97" box="[1204,1321,1248,1270]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="307">C. albertoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the mesonotum, which lacks lateral yellow vittae. Among other 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403F5F14FC13FA944B013D51" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1846" box="[993,1125,1310,1331]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403F5F14FC13FA944B013D51" box="[993,1125,1310,1331]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="307">Copestylum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403F5F14FB71FA944BB83D51" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[1155,1244,1310,1331]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tapia">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403F5F14FB71FA944BB83D51" box="[1155,1244,1310,1331]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="307">C. tapia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
most closely resembles 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403F5F14FC56FAB64A5B3D31" authority="(Hull, 1948)" baseAuthorityName="Hull" baseAuthorityYear="1948" box="[932,1343,1340,1363]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cupricolor">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403F5F14FC56FAB64BC13D33" box="[932,1189,1340,1361]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="307">Copestylum cupricolor</emphasis>
(Hull, 1948)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403F5F14FABCFAB74B0A3D13" authority="(Hull, 1950)" baseAuthorityName="Hull" baseAuthorityYear="1950" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lucilia">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403F5F14FABCFAB74CA83D12" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="307">Copestylum lucilia</emphasis>
(Hull, 1950)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403F5F14FB4EFAD14C953DF2" authority="(Hull, 1950)" baseAuthorityName="Hull" baseAuthorityYear="1950" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pertinax">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403F5F14FB4EFAD14C343DED" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="307">Copestylum pertinax</emphasis>
(Hull, 1950)
</taxonomicName>
in having sharply defined black vittae on the face, mesonotum without bristles, a scutellar depression, and tergites 3 and 4 with patches of white hairs. 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403F5F14FBBFFA5C4BC23D89" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[1101,1190,1494,1515]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tapia">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403F5F14FBBFFA5C4BC23D89" box="[1101,1190,1494,1515]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="307">C. tapia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from these species in lacking a yellow band at the apex to the mesonotum, and the peculiar long, white hairs at the apex of the sixth abdominal segment. Early stages of 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403F5F14FC68F9DB4C973E04" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Hancock &amp; Marcos-García" authorityYear="2007" box="[922,1011,1617,1638]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tapia">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403F5F14FC68F9DB4C973E04" box="[922,1011,1617,1638]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="307">C. tapia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are distinguished from other bromeliad 
<taxonomicName id="F4FF5AF9403F5F14FC73F9E54B613EE6" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1846" box="[897,1029,1647,1668]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403F5F14FC73F9E54B613EE6" box="[897,1029,1647,1668]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="307">Copestylum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
early stages by their subcyclindrical shape in cross-section, long, matted vestiture not in obvious, transverse rows, pupal spiracles with a coating of setae much longer than the width of a respiratory opening, and the posterior breathing tube not two times as wide as the pupal spiracles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3340217A403F5F14FCD4F8B64BB93F13" blockId="40.[806,1421,1852,1905]" pageId="40" pageNumber="307">
<emphasis id="018BFD68403F5F14FCD4F8B64CE53F33" box="[806,897,1852,1873]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="307">Biology:</emphasis>
Reared from larvae found in fallen, decaying bromeliads in cloud forest in 
<collectingCountry id="4BE861EA403F5F14FB8AF8D14BBD3F13" box="[1144,1241,1883,1905]" name="Ecuador" pageId="40" pageNumber="307">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
